William Hauber https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Hauber 0 William Hauber (May 20, 1891 – July 17, 1929) was an American film actor. He appeared in 66 films between 1913 and 1928. He was born in Brownsville, Minnesota, and died in California in a plane crash during aerial scouting for film locations during the production of the film The Aviator in 1929.
